instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Command flow from the digital twin to the physical building is orchestrated via the Ditto instance. Facility Managers or automated control logic issue control commands (e.g., switch state changes, actuator positions) through the UE5 front‑end, which are transmitted to Ditto over its WebSocket interface. Ditto then routes the command to the corresponding physical device through Eclipse Hono, following the same messaging topology used for telemetry. Each command is accompanied by a synchronous acknowledgement mechanism: UE5 only updates the rendered twin state after receiving a positive confirmation from the device (or from Ditto acknowledging receipt). Validation and conflict resolution are achieved implicitly by the deduplication and ordering guarantees of Hono’s messaging layer, while authentication or access control is implied by Ditto’s secure Edge‑to‑Edge communication framework, though explicit mechanisms are not described in the documents. "
]

